'''Barrett & Thomson''' was an American architectural firm based in [[Raleigh, North Carolina]] that functioned from c. 1900 to c. 1910. It was a partnership of '''Charles W. Barrett''' (1869–1947) and '''Frank K. Thomson''' (1872–1961).<ref name=ncarchitects>{{cite web|url=http://ncarchitects.lib.ncsu.edu/people/P000171 |title=North Carolina Architects & Builders: Barrett and Thomson (ca.1900–ca. 1910) |author=Catherine W. Bishir |year=2009}}</ref>
Two of the firm's various projects were selected to be on the U.S. [[National Register of Historic Places]].<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref>
Works include: *[[Jarvisburg Colored School]], built 1911, 7301 NC 158, [[Jarvisburg, North Carolina]] (Barrett and Thomson), NRHP-listed<ref name=nris/> *[[Woodlawn School (Mebane, North Carolina)|Woodlawn School]], N side NC 1921 0.15&nbsp;mi. W of jct. with NC 1920, [[Mebane, North Carolina]] (Barrett & Thomson), NRHP-listed<ref name=nris/>
