{{Infobox company | |name = Fundición Tipográfica Nacional |logo = |type = Defunct |genre = |foundation = [[Madrid, Spain]] (1915) |founder = |defunct = 1971 |location = [[Madrid, Spain]] |key_people = [[Carlos Winkow]], [[Enric Crous-Vidal]] |industry = [[Type foundry]] |num_employees = |revenue = |homepage = }}
''' Fundición Tipográfica Nacional ''' or the ''' Nacional Typefoundry''' was for many years the leading type foundry of [[Spain]]. It was founded in [[Madrid]] in 1915 and functioned there until bought out by [[Neufville Typefoundry|Fundición Tipográfica Neufville]] of [[Barcelona]] in 1971. It employed prestigious designers like [[Carlos Winkow]] and [[Enric Crous-Vidal]] and was noted for its bold and striking art deco faces.
